      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This DDL script creates a unique index named CARDDEMO.XAUTHFRD on the CARDDEMO.AUTHFRDS table. The index is composed of two columns: CARD_NUM, which is indexed in ascending order (ASC), and AUTH_TS, which is indexed in descending order (DESC). The 'COPY YES' clause indicates that copies of this index are permitted. The primary purpose of this index is to improve the performance of queries that filter or sort data based on CARD_NUM and AUTH_TS. By creating a unique index, the database system can quickly locate specific rows based on these columns, ensuring data integrity by enforcing uniqueness across the specified columns. This index is not called by any other programs or paragraphs, nor does it call any other programs or paragraphs. There is no error handling within this DDL script.",
